          It was a convincing win but all it has done is paper over the cracks I'm afraid. The 1 positive is that Wenger committed himself to buying a central defender in January. Nice finishes for all the non-penalty goals (although the penalty was very well taken too) but we were still way too open at the back, defended too high, many players out of position inviting a counter attack, terrible zonal marking etc etc, the same old crap that always happens with us. As for the fans singing "There's only one Arsene Wenger", there were only about 1,000 actually singing and they are the ones who likely never supported Arsenal before he took over and/or don't mind paying thousands a year to watch a perennial underachieving team, so if he thinks all is well now we beat a team that will finish 8th or below, he's severely mistaken.
